{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17596104","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17596104"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:10:37+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:10:37+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15394"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15394","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15394"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8085"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69835"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8085","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8085"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15394"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55291"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"},{"type":"tags","id":"10046"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19618"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19620"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69835","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/69835"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EConstipation can be divided into primary and secondary causes.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following represents a primary cause of chronic constipation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hyperparathyroidism","Hypothyroidism","Hypercalcaemia","Hypokalaemia","Dyssynergia"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHyperparathyroidism\u003C/strong\u003E can cause constipation through increased calcium levels, but it is a secondary cause. \u003Cstrong\u003EHypothyroidism\u003C/strong\u003E leads to constipation through decreased gut motility, but is also considered secondary. \u003Cstrong\u003EHypercalcaemia\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Ehypokalaemia\u003C/strong\u003E are metabolic disturbances that secondarily affect bowel function.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDyssynergia\u003C/strong\u003E is a primary defecation disorder where there is impaired coordination between abdominal, rectoanal and pelvic floor muscles during attempted defecation. This condition directly affects the defecation process and is therefore classified as a primary cause of constipation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Primary causes of constipation include neurological disorders, endocrine conditions, and defecation disorders.","Dyssynergia is a primary defecation disorder characterised by paradoxical contraction of pelvic floor muscles during attempted defecation."],"references":["Forootan M, Bagheri N, Darvishi M. Chronic constipation: A review of literature. Medicine (Baltimore). 2018 May;97(20):e10631. doi: 10.1097/MD.0000000000010631. PMID: 29768326; PMCID: PMC5976340.","Diaz S, Bittar K, Hashmi MF, et al. Constipation. [Updated 2023 Nov 12]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK513291/","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Scienc"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55291"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15394"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55291","links":{"self":"